Sweetheart Deal: Chapter Thirty-Five - Bottom Of The Ninth

Welcome to Nuevo Carcangel, circa 2174. A century has passed since a plague killed half of humanity. No one living now knows why some of the survivors are called chimeras, nor how the plague created them - if it did.
Christina Marlowe, a private investigator and a fox-type chimera, has other concerns. She's living in one of the biggest city-states. What technology used to exist is gone. She knows the trains and streetcars, her trusty revolver, and that she needs a big case.
Nathaniel Berrymount may be it. He's nervous at first and rightly so. The signs point to a sweetheart deal that's meant to collapse, leaving the victor with everything.
Marlowe will have to think and talk fast as events pile up. A Boss wants his blueprints back. What do the buns of The Warren want? And can she keep her client from falling for her?

In this chapter, Marlowe confronts Travis Delmar, the most powerful man at City Hall. The message? His schemes and deals are falling apart, and she's got a single word that he can't weasel out of.
But unexpected guests are the theme of the day, and not everyone survives a sweetheart deal that turns bitter.

Coming soon - Chapter Thirty-Six

Thanks for the feedback! When the idea popped into my head, I really just wanted to write something wholesome, while also showcasing something I haven’t seen tackled before in other stories. A lot of times in writing, you get a simple “oh they got pregnant and had a kid, and then they lived happily ever after,” without detailing any of the struggles that come with pregnancy and childbirth.

In the story there’s not a ton of conflict or strife because I wanted to show a snipped of a close to ideal scenario. It might not be the most entertaining when it comes to tension and such, but that’s exactly what I intended! I guess I’m a sucker for feel-good stories
